quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  25,68,"And those who do not worship any other deity along with Allah, and do not unjustly kill any living thing which Allah has forbidden, nor commit adultery; and whoever does this will receive punishment."
  25,69,"The punishment shall be increased for him on the Day of Resurrection, and he will remain in it forever, with humiliation."
  25,70,"Except one who repents and accepts faith and does good deeds – so Allah will turn their evil deeds into virtues; and Allah is Oft Forgiving, Most Merciful."
  25,71,"And whoever repents and does good deeds – so he has inclined towards Allah with repentance as was required."
  25,72,"And those who do not give false testimony, and when they pass near some indecency, they pass by it saving their honour."
  25,73,"And those who, when they are reminded of the signs of their Lord, do not fall deaf and blind upon them."
  25,74,"And who submit, “Our Lord, soothe our eyes with our wives and our children, and make us leaders of the pious.”"
  25,75,"They will be rewarded the highest position in heaven, the recompense of their patience, and they will be welcomed with honour and greetings of peace."
  25,76,"They shall abide in it forever; what an excellent abode and place of stay."
  25,77,"Say (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) “You have no value before My Lord if you do not worship Him; so you have denied – therefore the punishment that remains, will occur.”"
